pe\":\"observability_scout\",\"category\":\"code_quality\",\"title\":\"Thread executionId through network proxy logs\",\"description\":\"The network proxy in networkProxy.ts logs blocked/allowed requests with host and port but never includes the executionId that owns the proxy instance. Additionally, client socket errors on line 86 are silently swallowed. Pass executionId into startFilterProxy, include it in all log entries, and log client-side socket errors. Add per-execution counters for allowed/blocked requests emitted at proxy cleanup.\",\"reasoning\":\"When a persona execution fails due to network issues, operators must cross-reference proxy logs by timestamp to correlate with execution logs. Missing executionId in proxy logs makes this error-prone. Swallowed client errors (line 86) mean connection resets from the sandboxed process leave no diagnostic trace, making network-related failures invisible.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":2,\"impact\":6,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:58:37.562Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:58:37.562Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":1,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T11:58:38.149Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013TYeF9AnQVkaMF9mNzsQWk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018xrwZPGUm9djAY4gnhWpxk","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"a4c7fd70-a94d-45a9-a95d-94fb1b2e663c\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"observability_scout\",\n    \"category\": \"code_quality\",\n    \"title\": \"Audit and fix swallowed exceptions across worker\",\n    \"description\": \"Multiple catch blocks silently discard errors: executor.ts:71 swallows the execution promise error without any trace, networkProxy.ts:34 swallows URL parse errors without logging, networkProxy.ts:86 swallows client socket errors, credentialInjector.ts:81-82 swallows readdir failures, and sandbox.ts:153 swallows chmod failures. Add contextual warn-level logging to each of these catch blocks with the relevant executionId and operation name.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Swallowed exceptions are the number one cause of invisible failures. When a credential directory is inaccessible, a proxy URL is malformed, or a socket resets unexpectedly, these events leave zero trace in logs. During incident investigation, the absence of error logs leads operators to wrong conclusions. Each of these is a 1-line fix that dramatically improves diagnosability.\",\n    \"effort\": 2,\n    \"impact\": 7,\n    \"risk\": 1\n  }'","description":"Submit idea 3"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":997,"cache_read_input_tokens":54055,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":997},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id"